cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.MM, cs.AR, cs.SY 

Reasoning: 

- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on WLANs and their technical requirements, key technologies, and performance evaluations. 
- cs.IT (Information Theory) is also likely as the paper discusses the physical layer enhancements and power efficiency of IEEE 802.11ax. 
- cs.MM (Multimedia) is a possible category as the paper mentions the demand for quality of services (QoS) in WLANs. 
- cs.AR (Hardware Architecture) is a possible category as the paper discusses the technical objectives and requirements of IEEE 802.11ax. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is a possible category as the paper evaluates the performance requirements of IEEE 802.11ax using a simulation platform.
